            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " when they go up to a door to drop off an order. Now apparently operators of heavy trucks, including garbage trucks, need to be extra vigilant. According to an NBC New York report, Mario Cassanova saw the sanitation worker was hitching a 30-yard dumpster to the back of the garbage truck when he jumped into the cab and threatened the worker who was inside. Then he took off, doing as much damage as he could.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
