            "text": "Not only did Cassanova take out a number of cars parked on the side of the road in Brooklyn, he swiped light poles and trees as well. A reporter showed how there were still car parts strewn all over sidewalks in the area as owners emerged from their residents to survey the damage.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
